    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2012-09-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-09-20T20:42:10Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Buffett Rule Act of 2012 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow taxpayers to donate an amount (not less than $1), in addition to any tax owed, which shall be deposited in the general fund of the Treasury and transferred to an account used to reduce the public debt.&nbsp; Requires such donation to be designated on&nbsp;a taxpayer's income tax return at the time such return is filed.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>81</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2012-09-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Passed House without amendment</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2012-09-24T20:36:29Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)</b></p> <p>Buffett Rule Act of 2012 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow taxpayers to donate an amount (not less than $1), in addition to any tax owed, which shall be deposited in the general fund of the Treasury and transferred to an account used to reduce the public debt.&nbsp; Requires such donation to be designated on&nbsp;a taxpayer's income tax return at the time such return is filed.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
